<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}-{9}{y}=-{30}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{5}{x}-{5}{y}=-{60}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{6},{6}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}+-{9}{y}=-{30}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}=-{30}-{\left(-{9}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{-{30}-{\left(-{9}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{4}}}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{5}{\left(\frac{{-{30}-{\left(-{9}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{4}}}}\right)}+-{5}{y}=-{60}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle\frac{{5}}{{-{{4}}}}\cdot{\left(-{30}\right)}-\frac{{5}}{{-{{4}}}}{\left(-{9}\right)}{y}+-{5}{y}=-{60}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{37.5}-{\left(-{11.25}\right)}{y}+-{5}{y}=-{60}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{11.25}{y}+{\left(-{5}\right)}{y}=-{60}-{37.5}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{11.25}{y}+{\left(-{5}\right)}{y}=-{97.5}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{11.25}+{\left(-{5}\right)}\right)}{y}=-{97.5}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{16.25}{y}=-{97.5}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-\frac{{97.5}}{{-{{16.25}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}={6}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}+-{9}{\left({6}\right)}=-{30}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}+{\left(-{54}\right)}=-{30}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}=-{30}-{\left(-{54}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}={24}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{24}}{{-{{4}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-{6}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left(-{6},{6}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

